\subsection{Achieved rate in STIM}
Based on the above description of STIM, the achieved rate in STIM can be
written as 
\begin{eqnarray}
R_{\mbox{{\scriptsize STIM}}}&\hspace{-1mm} = & \hspace{-1mm}
\frac{1}{N+L-1} \bigg[ \underbrace{k{\left\lfloor \log_2{n_t}\right\rfloor}}_{\mbox{antenna index bits}}
+ \underbrace{\Big\lfloor \log_2{N \choose k}\Big\rfloor }_{\mbox{slot index bits}} \nonumber \\
& & + \ \underbrace{k\log_2 |{\mathbb A}|}_{\mbox{modulation symbol bits}} \bigg] \quad \mbox{bpcu}.
\label{stim_rate1}
\end{eqnarray}
